SUMMARY:Invasive Plant Removal (Matthews)
DESCRIPTION:Join HAWK for a hands-on morning of conservation as we continue our successful effort to remove invasive plants at Sardis Park! Together we’ll tackle Autumn Olive & Ligustrum\, helping native plants and wildlife thrive.\nWe will also plant trees & spread mulch.\nPlease wear long pants and long sleeves\, and bring gloves\, water\, and pruning tools (pruners\, loppers\, etc.). We’ll have some extra tools available on site.\nCome lend a hand\, enjoy the outdoors\, and make a real difference for our local habitat!\nHAWK (Habitat and Wildlife Keepers) is the Matthews chapter of the NC Wildlife Federation\n \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/invasive-plant-removal-matthews-2/
END:VEVENT
