SUMMARY:High Country Wild Chartering Ceremony (Blowing Rock)
DESCRIPTION:High Country Wild is one of NCWF’s newest Community Wildlife Chapters. The chapter protects\, conserves\, and restores wildlife and habitat in Ashe and Watauga County. The chapter brings the local community together with opportunities to restore habitat\, connect with nature\, and learn about important wildlife and habitat topics in the region. \nJoin us as we get together for a fun evening to celebrate and officially launch the new Chapter. This is an opportunity to learn more about High Country Wild\, meet NCWF staff and local chapter leaders\, and get involved with conservation at the grassroots level. Big thanks to Blue Ridge Conservancy for letting us use their amazing conservation campus as our venue. We’ll kick off the event with a tour of the campus to search for critters and identify plants. \nDrinks will be available alongside plenty of snacks. Bring your ideas\, curiosity\, and maybe a few random wildlife facts. All are welcome! Space is limited so please sign up now. \nREGISTER HERE
URL:https://ncwf.org/event/high-country-wild-chartering-ceremony-blowing-rock/
CATEGORIES:Featured
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://ncwf.org/wp-content/uploads/Charteringceromony-1.jpg
